:'''c.''' In other forms: ƒÉgo, ''amb&acirc;ges;'' pƒÉc-, pƒÉc-iscor, '''p&acirc;cis''' (p&acirc;x); sƒÉg-ax, ''s&acirc;gus, s&acirc;ga;'' mƒÉc-er, ''m&acirc;cero;'' fƒÉg- (&phi;&alpha;&gamma;&epsilon;&iota;&nu;), ''f&acirc;gus.'' (Contrary to analogy, ''ƒÉ'' remains short in dƒÉnunt, from dƒÉ-in-unt, vide Friedrich Wilhelm Ritschl, ''Priscae Latinitatis Monumenta Epigraphica'', l. 1. page 17.)
